of blood and death.  She wiped the rapidly drying liquid from her sword onto the torn leggings of her latest Hal fling victim with a satisfied yet hate-filled smile.<br>
<br>
5 months ago, the Ambassador’s daughter would not have, even in her wildest dreams, imagined this to be her fate.  She was born and raised to a life of politics, and was expected to follow in her father’s footsteps.  Other than frequently attending council meetings, her childhood was sheltered from the harsh truths of Norath.  She had never been beyond the boundaries of Neriak.  Her father doted on his only child, and she was not permitted to know the identify of her mother.<br>
<br>
Then is one swift act of deceit and betrayal,, life as she knew it was ripped away.  Her father was poisoned, leaving him a half-witted drunkard incapable of even the most basic speech.  In the malady that followed, it was rare to see him outside of the Maiden’s Fancy.  The title of Ambassador became a meaningless label.<br>
<br>
Neither the assassin’s identity, nor his affiliations are known to Natori.  The only information available to her were the bits of information offered by Darkrayne of the Violent Harvest, the priest who was left responsible for her care and instruction.<br>
<br>
Natori both loathes Darkrayne, and holds him in intrigue, each bit of knowledge shifting the tides one way or another as to which was the stronger sentiment.   She won’t admit to the admiration, the growing attachment, not the lust she feels.<br>
<br>
Darkrayne insisted that she leave the life of a politician behind, and instead, allow her sword to do her mediating for her.  At first she strongly resisted this change, but with time, she found the lifestyle tolerable, even preferable, leaving her childish spoiled and refined ways behind her.<br>
<br>
Recently, she was permitted to attend a meeting of the client harvest.  She sat mesmerized through the ceremonies, drinking in every moment of the sacred rites of hatred and pain.  She now hopes to take her place in the ranks of the Violent Harvest as a warrior.  (***OOC*** Dark Elf, Warrior, Level 7, for a little bit anyway Thanks again for letting me attend Darkrayne's binding, and kudos to everyone else too. ***OOC***) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#8E236B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/uxarethsthanos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xareth S thanos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dread Overlord</span><br>  Posts: 239<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/20/02 3:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=169.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Ambassador's daughter picks up a sword</span><hr size=1> Seek a Dread Overlord of our order, young warrioress. We are Shaede, Pravdameer, and myself.<br>
