<br>
Out loud, she called out to him, “What manner of magic is this, an animal that speaks, healing magics that don’t do their work instantly?”<br>
<br>
The bear let out a deep rumbling laugh, “I come from a land far from here, where the ice never melts, and the ground beneath never sees the light of day.  As for the fur,” The bear waved his arms in almost a manlike fashion, and before her stood one of a race she’d only heard about, “Tis but an illusion.”<br>
<br>
Natori wrinkled her nose, “You looked better as a bear.”<br>
<br>
Again, that laugh, “Now, about my proposal?” the man asked as he reverted to the animalistic form.<br>
<br>
“I don’t like you, but for now we share a common enemy.  You kill the more seasoned, I keep the novices off of you so they don’t interrupt your magic, you get their grass necklaces and I keep any of the skullcaps we might find? It sounds to simple.”<br>
<br>
